(0.5)`, positioning it at (0, 0) means the top-left corner is at (0, 0). If you 
do call `setOrigin(0.5)`, the center is at (0, 0).\n\nWhen a component does:\n``
`typescript\nthis.background = createInkBackground(this.scene, width, height, bg
Color, strokeColor);\n(this.background).setOrigin(0.5);\n```\n\nIt fixes the ori
gin after creation. But if another component uses `createFallbackRect` directly,
it already has origin 0.5. If a developer switches from `createInkBackground` to
`createFallbackRect` or vice versa, they might forget to add/remove the `setOrig
in(0.5)` call, causing visual bugs.\n\nThe PRD-004 section 3.3 says:\n"回退元素
的尺寸与预期纹理一致，边框颜色与 UITheme 协调，透明度 alpha ≥ 0.8"\n\nAnd the de
sign spec says:\n"回退状态下组件的交互功能必须保持可用"\n\nIt doesn\'t explicitl
y say origin must be consistent, but having two "create background rectangle" fu
nctions with different origins is a clear maintainability issue.\n\nOne more thi
ng to check: does `createInkBackground` need the `key` parameter for warn? No, `
createInkBackground` is for when you intentionally want an ink background, not a
s a fallback. The fallback-specific function is `createFallbackRect`.\n\nActuall
y, I just realized something. Looking at `UIButton.ts`:\n```typescript\nif (text
ure && hasTexture(this.scene, texture)) {\n  this.background = this.scene.add.im
age(0, 0, texture);\n  this.background.setDisplaySize(width, height);\n} else {\
n  this.background = createInkBackground(this.scene, width, height, bgColor, str
okeColor);\n  (this.background).setOrigin(0.5);\n}\n```\n\nAnd `UIPanel.ts`:\n``
`typescript\nif (texture && hasTexture(this.scene, texture)) {\n  this.backgroun
d = this.scene.add.image(0, 0, texture);\n  this.background.setDisplaySize(width
, height);\n} else {\n  this.background = createInkBackground(this.scene, width,
height, bgColor, strokeColor);\n  (this.background).setOrigin(0.5);\n}\n```\n\nB
oth components manually set origin to 0.5 after `createInkBackground`. But if th
ey used `createFallbackRect`, they wouldn\'t need to. The fact that both compone
nts have to manually add `setOrigin(0.5)` after `createInkBackground` suggests t
hat `createInkBackground` should just include it.\n\nThis is definitely a Major 
